headline: DVA Q1 Earnings Call: Cyber Incident, Volume Decline, and Policy Updates Shape Outlook
summary: Dialysis provider DaVita Inc. (NYSE:DVA) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025 as sales rose 5% year on year to $3.22 billion. Its non-GAAP EPS of $2 per share was 1% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
